comment: Len (PHX) and Randolph (MEM) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
Len (PHX) jumps from point A to point B and makes body contact with Conley (MEM) that affects his shot attempt.
RHH and RATR show that Len (PHX) and Leuer (PHX) maintain legal guarding position as they contest Randolph's (MEM) shot attempt.
Leuer (PHX) makes contact with Gasol's (MEM) arm that affects his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Gasol (MEM) sets the screen on Knight (PHX) and gives him room to avoid the contact.

RATR and R-Slash show that as Gasol (MEM) catches the ball, Leuer (PHX) fouls Gasol's right arm, affecting his shot. R-Slash shows Randolph makes contact with Len (PHX), but contact does not appear to affect his movement into Gasol before ball is lost.
Green (MEM) and Bledsoe (PHX) make incidental contact with one another while going after a rebound.
After the dribble handoff, Tucker (PHX) sets the screen on Conley (MEM) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Gasol (MEM) clamps Leuer's (PHX) arm, affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Len (PHX) committed a goaltending violation was overturned.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Knight (PHX) was upheld. Memphis was awarded possession and the clock was adjusted to 00:00.8.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the officials determined there was a clock malfunction and the game clock was reset to 00:00.5.
